A By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –
Chief Justice of Nigeria, Justice Onnoghen on Tuesday shunned the Code Of Conduct Tribunal (CCT) sitting in Abuja. Recall that the federal
government is accusing the CJN of failing to declare his assets when he was
sworn in. The tribunal has begun the
day’s sitting in Onnoghen’s absence, with a consortium of senior lawyers again
appearing for him. Recall further that the
defendant had approached a Federal High Court to challenge the jurisdiction of
the tribunal to hear the case. Counsel to the CJN told the
court that the defendant was not properly served with court summons. Details Later…